context.p:
The plugin installs a series of Eclipse wizards for easy creation of documents. If you use these wizards, automatically completes the following details:
the system ID, or schema location of a new XML document;
the minimal markup of a DocBook article, or the namespace declarations of a Relax NG schema.

ul.li:
Schema URL - specifies the path to the schema file. When you
              select a file,  analyzes
              its content and tries to fill the rest of the dialog box;

Schema type - allows you to select the schema type. The
              following options are available: XML Schema, DTD, RelaxNG XML syntax, RelaxNG compact
              syntax, and NVDL;

Add optional content - if you select this option, the
              elements, and attributes defined in the XML Schema as optional, are generated in the
              skeleton XML document;

XML Schema 1.0 - Sets the minVersion
              attribute to 1.0 and the maxVersion attribute to
                1.1;
